Notaulus as short to moderately long groove somewhat distant from anterolateral margin of mesoscutum ( Figs 24, 25 ). Mesoscutum with dense, shallow, indistinct punctures, weakly granulate to almost smooth between punctures, usually with longitudinal wrinkles medioposteriorly. Scutellum with lateral longitudinal carinae reaching its posterior end but usually not joining posteriorly (
Fig. 25
). Foveate groove of mesopleuron situated in anterior 0.6–0.7 of mesopleuron, oblique, moderately broad, sharp and crenulate, not reaching anterior margin of mesopleuron (
Fig. 24
). Mesopleuron finely and shallowly punctate, smooth and shining between punctures. Propodeum granulate, dorsolateral area usually very finely punctate, with short wrinkles adjacent to carinae. Basal part of propodeum short, 0.35 × as long as apical area, with few longitudinal subparallel wrinkles. Propodeal spiracle rather big, round, separated from pleural carina by ≤ 0.5 × diameter of spiracle, often spiracle adjacent to pleural carina. Apical area flat, anteriorly broad and usually rounded.

Fore wing (
Fig. 1
) with veins Rs + 2 r and Rs angled 120 to 135 °. Vein 2 rs-m more than twice as long as abscissa of M between 2 rs-m and 2 m-cu . Hind wing with cu 1 & cu-a distinctly inclivous. Hind femur 4.45 × as long as broad, 0.84 × as long as tibia.
